/* Application Structure Plan: The application adopts a thematic section-based dashboard approach. The main App component manages the activeSection and searchTerm states, determining which content block is currently visible and how it's filtered. Navigation is driven by the Navbar and CategoryTabs, allowing users to switch between different thematic news feeds (e.g., "Home" / "AI & Tech", "Automotive", "Gadget with AI", "Robotics", "Machine Learning", "Reviews", "News", "Gallery", "Contact"). Each section displays a curated list of articles relevant to its theme, presented in a responsive grid. This structure was chosen for usability because it provides clear, distinct content areas, allowing users to quickly jump to their area of interest without navigating to separate pages, thus facilitating easy exploration and understanding of diverse content within a single interactive view. The search functionality now filters articles within the active section, enhancing content discoverability. The "Generate AI Headline" button in the Hero section remains a standalone interactive element, not tied to section navigation. */
/* Visualization & Content Choices: Report Info (News Articles) -> Goal (Inform, Explore) -> Viz/Presentation Method (Article Cards with text, author, date, and placeholder images) -> Interaction (Click to 'Read More' - currently placeholder, Category Filtering, Keyword Search) -> Justification (Familiar, scannable format for news; filtering and search allow focused exploration) -> Library/Method (HTML/CSS/React components, JS for filtering and state management). Report Info (Categories) -> Goal (Organize, Navigate) Filter) -> Viz/Presentation Method (Clickable Buttons/Tabs) -> Interaction (Select category to change displayed articles) -> Justification (Intuitive for content segmentation) -> Library/Method (HTML/CSS/React components, JS for state management). Report Info (Search) -> Goal (Inform, Filter) -> Viz/Presentation Method (Input field) -> Interaction (Type to filter articles) -> Justification (Standard search pattern for content refinement) -> Library/Method (HTML/CSS/React components, JS for filtering). Loading State -> Goal (Inform User) -> Viz/Presentation Method (Spinning Loader with descriptive text) -> Interaction (Visual feedback) -> Justification (Indicates ongoing process, better than blank screen) -> Library/Method (HTML/CSS animation). */
/* CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. */
